=== TASK ===
# Media Management & Image Optimization

## Overview
Create a robust media management system that enables uploading, transforming, and delivering high-quality images for Roam Resort listings, host profiles, and editorial content. The system should support client-side cropping, on-the-fly transformations, responsive srcset generation, and delivery through Cloudinary (Media CDN & Uploads). Ensure security, performance, and a premium editorial UI consistent with the Roam Resort brand. All code and configurations must guard against null/undefined values before using array methods, initialize arrays with proper defaults, and validate API responses defensively.

---

## Components to Build

1) Cloudinary Integration Layer
- Purpose: Abstract Cloudinary uploads, signed uploads (server-side if required), transformations, and CDN delivery.
- Features:
  - Client-side direct upload to Cloudinary with unsigned or signed presets (depending on security model).
  - Transformation presets for hero, gallery, thumbnails (resize, crop, quality, blur, blur-up, focal point).
  - Generating responsive srcset/traced images and delivering optimized variants via Cloudinary URLs.
  - Fallbacks for offline/failed uploads with retry logic and status reporting.
- Data Outputs:
  - Media asset metadata: public_id, asset_url, secure_url, width, height, format, bytes, duration (for videos if supported), resource_type, created_at, transformations_applied, tags, gallery_mapping_id.

2) Frontend Media Uploader & Cropping UI
- Purpose: Provide host/admin users with an intuitive UI to upload and crop images client-side, preview variants, and assign to listings or profiles.
- Features:
  - Drag-and-drop plus file picker with client-side type/size validation.
  - Client-side cropping UI (aspect ratios per asset type: listing hero, gallery image, avatar/profile, editorial banner).
  - Live preview of transformed variants (thumbnail, gallery, hero, etc.) using Cloudinary transformed URLs or client-side canvas crop previews.
  - Image metadata capture: alt text, caption, focal point coordinates.
  - Progress indicators, error handling, and retry options.
- Data Outputs:
  - Cropped image data (blob/original), crop geometry, alt text, caption, focal point, associated entity (listing_id, profile_id, editorial_id).

3) Media Asset Service & Database Mapping
- Purpose: Persist media asset references and map them to listings, hosts, and editorial content.
- Data Model:
  - MediaAsset: id, public_id, secure_url, width, height, format, bytes, resource_type, type (listing_gallery, listing_hero, host_avatar, editorial_gallery, editorial_hero), owner_type (listing, host, editorial), owner_id, caption, alt_text, focal_point_x, focal_point_y, created_at, updated_at, transformations (JSON).
  - MediaAssetRelation: id, media_asset_id, entity_type (listing, host, editorial), entity_id, position (ordering), created_at.
- Features:
  - Safe mapping of media assets to multiple entities with ordering for galleries.
  - Null-safe getters and guards when mapping to UI.
  - Validation to ensure arrays are initialized: use data ?? [] and Array.isArray checks before mapping.

4) API Layer
- Endpoints (REST/GraphQL as chosen by project):
  - POST /api/media/upload (direct Cloudinary upload orchestration)
  - POST /api/media/upload/crop (save crop metadata and initiate transform)
  - GET /api/media/:id (retrieve asset metadata and URLs)
  - GET /api/media/entity/:entityType/:entityId (list assets for a given listing/host/editorial)
  - PATCH /api/media/:id/transform (apply/record additional transformations)
  - DELETE /api/media/:id (soft delete and remove associations)
- Security:
  - Authenticated access; role checks for hosts vs admins.
  - Validate incoming data; ensure arrays and objects exist before use.
- Validation:
  - Ensure Cloudinary public_id and URLs are present before returning to client.
  - Guard against missing fields and provide defaults (e.g., width/height 0, bytes 0).

5) Image Transformation Presets & srcset Generation
- Presets:
  - hero_large: width 1200-1600, crop/fit via cloudinary, quality auto
  - gallery_thumb: width 300-600, crop, quality auto
  - listing_avatar: width 200, height 200, crop
  - editorial_banner: width 1600, height 420, crop
- Responsive srcset:
  - Generate multiple width variants (e.g., 320, 480, 768, 1024, 1400) with appropriate dpr2/dpr3 scaling.
  - Provide srcset attribute values and sizes hints for responsive loading.
- Delivery:
  - Use Cloudinary CDN delivery with secure URLs, auto format (webp/jpg), progressive loading where applicable.

6) Admin/Host Portal Pages Integration
- Pages:
  - page_011, page_003, page_002, page_001 correspond to listing creation/edit, host dashboard, editorial content, and admin panel for inquiries/media.
- Features:
  - Image upload components on listing/edit forms.
  - Gallery management with drag-and-drop reordering.
  - Display of image thumbnails with alt-text, captions, and transformation previews.
  - Ability to toggle visibility on a per-image basis.

