## User Experience Flow

1) Host/Admin navigates to a listing/editorial content page.
2) Clicks "Add Images" or drags files into uploader area.
3) Client-side validations occur (type, size, aspect ratios).
4) User crops image using the ImageCropper with preset aspect ratios:
   - Hero: 16:9 or 3:1 responsive; Gallery: 4:3; Avatar: 1:1
5) Cropping completes; uploader shows progress; upon success, the image is uploaded to Cloudinary (signed or unsigned as configured).
6) Backend stores asset metadata and maps the asset to the appropriate entity (listing, host, or editorial).
7) UI displays gallery with responsive thumbnails and cropped hero preview; assets have alt text and captions editable.
8) Admin can reorder gallery, edit metadata, and remove assets; assets are persisted with safe defaults.
9) On publish, the system serves assets via Cloudinary URLs with proper srcset for responsive loading.

