## Development Prompts for AI Tool

- Build a CloudinaryService.ts to encapsulate:
  - Direct upload logic (unsigned vs signed), error handling, retry policy
  - Transformation URL builders for hero, gallery, avatar
  - srcset generation utility: given base URL, produce array of URLs with widths [320, 480, 768, 1024, 1400] and DPR variants
  - A safe interface returning asset metadata with strict null checks

- Create a MediaUploader component:
  - Supports drag-and-drop, click-to-upload
  - Validates file type/size with constants
  - Integrates ImageCropper component for client-side cropping
  - After crop, calls Cloudinary upload, then POSTs to /api/media/upload with payload including crop data and alt/caption
  - Maintains assets state: useState<MediaAsset[]>([])

- Implement an ImageCropper:
  - Accepts an image blob or URL; provides three aspect ratio presets
  - Outputs cropped image region coordinates and a data blob
  - Provides live preview of cropped result

- Build a MediaAssetService in the backend:
  - Prisma/ORM models for MediaAsset and MediaAssetRelation
  - Endpoints for CRUD and association with listings/hosts/editorials
  - Defensive data handling: validate and coerce responses to safe defaults

- Implement API routes:
  - /api/media/upload: handle file upload, call CloudinaryService.upload, persist MediaAsset, return safe response
  - /api/media/:id: return sanitized asset data
  - /api/media/entity/:entityType/:entityId: fetch assets with proper ordering
  - /api/media/:id/transform: update transformations and regenerate URLs if needed
  - Use middlewares for auth, role checks, and input validation

- Implement data mapping and safety guards:
  - When mapping assets to UI, do: Array.isArray(assets) ? assets.map(...) : []
  - When reading response data: const assets = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Initialize arrays in useState: const [assets, setAssets] = useState<MediaAsset[]>([])

- Integrate with pages:
  - page_011, page_003, page_002, page_001 should render media management sections where appropriate
  - Ensure gallery editing supports reorder by drag-and-drop with persisted ordering

- Testing:
  - Unit tests for Cloudinary URL builders, srcset generator, and guards
  - Integration tests for upload flow and asset association
  - E2E tests simulating host uploading, cropping, and gallery management

---

## Notes on Compliance with Runtime Safety Rules
- Always guard array operations: (items ?? []).map(...), Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
- Use nullish coalescing wherever API results are used: const items = data ?? [].
- Initialize useState with correct types: useState<MediaAsset[]>([]).
- Validate API response shapes before usage: const assetList = Array.isArray(resp?.data?.assets) ? resp.data.assets : [].
- Use optional chaining for nested API objects: asset?.url, asset?.public_id.
- Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.

